# Emails

CSA Admin uses two types of emails to communicate with your members:

- [**Automatic emails**](/mail_templates): sent automatically during specific events (new invoice, renewal, activity reminder, ...). You can customize their content and activate/deactivate them.
- [**Newsletters**](/newsletters): group emails that you compose and send manually (or schedule) to all or part of your members.

Both types use the same template language and formatting options described below.

## Liquid Template Language {#liquid}

Email templates use the [Liquid](https://shopify.github.io/liquid) template language, which lets you insert dynamic member-specific data and add conditional logic. Despite a "group" sending, the content of each email is generated individually based on the information of each member (name, language, membership, ...).

### Displaying Data

Use double curly braces to insert a value:

~~~ liquid
<p>Hello {{ member.name }},</p>
<p>Your next delivery is on {{ basket.delivery.date }}.</p>
~~~

### Conditions

Use `{% if %}` to show content only when a condition is met:

~~~ liquid
{% if basket.contents.size > 0 %}
  <h2><%= BasketContent.model_name.human(count: 2) %></h2>
  ...
{% endif %}
~~~

You can use `and`, `or`, as well as `{% elsif %}` and `{% else %}` to combine conditions:

~~~ liquid
{% if membership.trial_baskets_count > 0 %}
  <p>You are still in your trial period ({{ membership.trial_baskets_count }} <%= Basket.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %> remaining).</p>
{% elsif membership.activity_participations_missing_count > 0 %}
  <p>You still have {{ membership.activity_participations_missing_count }} activity(s) to complete.</p>
{% else %}
  <p>Everything is up to date, thank you!</p>
{% endif %}
~~~

### Loops

Use `{% for %}` to repeat content for each item in a list:

~~~ liquid
<ul>
  {% for content in basket.contents %}
    <li>{{ content.product }} ({{ content.quantity }})</li>
  {% endfor %}
</ul>
~~~

## Formatting Tags {#formatting-tags}

In addition to standard HTML, several special formatting tags are available:

**Highlight block** — Displays content in a colored highlight box, useful for important announcements:

~~~ liquid
{% highlight %}
  <p><strong>📣 Important!</strong></p>
  <p>Your <%= Basket.model_name.human.downcase %> will be extra large this week.</p>
{% endhighlight %}
~~~

**Lowlight block** — Displays content in a subtle grey box, useful for secondary information:

~~~ liquid
{% lowlight %}
  <p>Manage your registrations from
    <a href="{{ member.activities_url }}">your account</a>.</p>
{% endlowlight %}
~~~

**Button** — Displays a prominent call-to-action button. Pass the name of a variable containing the URL:

~~~ liquid
{% button member.activities_url %}
  Sign up for an activity
{% endbutton %}
~~~

## Data Preview {#data-preview}

When editing an email template or a newsletter template, a preview panel is displayed below the code editor. This preview shows your template rendered with sample data for each language.

Below each preview, a data panel shows the exact data structure available to your template. This data is generated semi-randomly from your actual organization data. You can modify the values in this panel to test how your template renders with different scenarios (e.g. empty <%= BasketContent.model_name.human.downcase %>, zero missing activities, etc.).

> The data preview is the best way to discover all available variables and test your template. Each type of email template has its own set of available data — always check the preview panel to see what's available.

## Common Liquid Variables {#variables}

Here is a quick reference of the most commonly used variables across email templates. Not all variables are available in every template — always check the [data preview](#data-preview) for the specific template you're editing.

### `member`

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `member.name` | Full name |
| `member.balance` | Current account balance (formatted) |
| `member.annual_fee` | Annual fee amount (formatted) |
| `member.page_url` | Link to the member's account page |
| `member.billing_url` | Link to the member's billing page |
| `member.deliveries_url` | Link to the member's deliveries page |
| `member.activities_url` | Link to the member's activities page |
| `member.absences_url` | Link to the member's absences page |
| `member.membership_renewal_url` | Link to the membership renewal page |

### `membership`

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `membership.start_date` | Membership start date (localized) |
| `membership.end_date` | Membership end date (localized) |
| `membership.state` | Current state |
| `membership.renewal_state` | Renewal state |
| `membership.trial_baskets_count` | Remaining trial <%= Basket.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %> |
| `membership.basket_size.name` | Name of the <%= BasketSize.model_name.human.downcase %> |
| `membership.depot.name` | Name of the depot |
| `membership.basket_complement_names` | Comma-separated list of complement names |
| `membership.activity_participations_demanded_count` | Total participations requested |
| `membership.activity_participations_accepted_count` | Validated participations |
| `membership.activity_participations_missing_count` | Remaining participations to complete |
| `membership.absences_included` | Number of included absences |
| `membership.absences_remaining` | Remaining included absences |

### `basket`

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `basket.delivery.date` | Delivery date (localized) |
| `basket.description` | <%= BasketSize.model_name.human %> description |
| `basket.complements_description` | Complements description |
| `basket.size.name` | Name of the <%= BasketSize.model_name.human.downcase %> |
| `basket.depot.name` | Name of the depot |
| `basket.quantity` | Quantity |
| `basket.contents` | List of <%= BasketContent.model_name.human(count: 2).downcase %> (use in a `for` loop) |

### `invoice`

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `invoice.number` | Invoice number |
| `invoice.date` | Invoice date (localized) |
| `invoice.entity_type` | Type of invoice (e.g. "Membership", "Shop::Order") |
| `invoice.amount` | Total amount (formatted) |
| `invoice.missing_amount` | Remaining unpaid amount (formatted) |
| `invoice.overdue_notices_count` | Number of overdue reminders sent |
